&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Registered Nurse to join the Pre-Operative Assessment Team. The post offers the right candidate the opportunity to develop both professionally and clinically with access to a wide range of educational opportunities. As part of the team you will have the opportunity to promote a nurse led service and autonomous practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pre-Operative Assessment is an integral part of our inpatient and day case service and we have just moved into a brand new state of the art hospital. During Pre-Operative Assessment the patient has the opportunity to discuss the procedure with a Clinician and ensure their stay is trouble free thus ensuring that they return home as soon as possible following treatment. This service also contributes to the effective utilisation of resources and improving the patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must possess the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- RGN Qualification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Minimum of 3 years post registration experience within a surgical speciality within the past 5 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Evidence of post registration development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- NMC Registration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- ENB 998 or equivalent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal chat please contact Senior Sister Margaret Pryce on (01922) 721172 ext 7295.&lt;/p&gt;
